<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF206-968-924  </DOCNO><DOCID>06 968 924.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Jan 17 1989 v3 n3 p44(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ruby Systems extends StarDrive line of hard drives. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mathews, Renee.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ruby Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Ruby Systems 40DXS StarDrive (Disk drive) (product introduction)Ruby Systems 40DXQ StarDrive (Disk drive) (product introduction)Ruby Systems 80DX StarDrive (Disk drive) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Hard DiskFunctional CapabilitiesProduct IntroductionPrice.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ruby Systems extends StarDrive line of hard drivesandM;MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.andP;  -- Ruby Systems Inc. has extended its StarDrive lineof hard drives for the Mac.andM;The latest additions to the StarDrive series include 30-, 40-, 45-, 60- and80-Mbyte models.andP;  Each drive comes with Next Generation StarDisk formattingand disk-partitioning software.andM;The 30-, 45- and 60-Mbyte models, based on Seagate drive mechanisms, haveaverage access times of 38 milliseconds to 40 milliseconds.andP;  Two 40-Mbyteoptions are available:andM;* The 40DXS, at $812, uses a Seagate mechanism with an average access time of40 milliseconds.andM;* The 40DXQ, at $952, uses a Quantum mechanism with a caching system thatcuts access times to 12 milliseconds to 14 milliseconds on partitioneddrives, the company said.andM;Ruby's 80-Mbyte 80DX StarDrive is also based on a Quantum mechanism thatdelivers similar performance.andM;External versions are $717 for the 30DX, $812 for the 40DXS, $952 for the40DXQ, $908 for the 45DX, $936 for the 60DX and $1,384 for the 80DX.andO;Internal models are priced at $80 less than the corresponding externalversion.andP;  Ruby Systems also offers the StarDrive 60TX, a $990, 60-Mbyte tapedrive, and the StarDrive 150tX, a $1,390, 150-Mbyte model.andM;Ruby Systems is located at 188 S. Whisman Road, Mountain View, Calif.andP;  94041;(415) 967-1187; (800) 888-1668.andO;</TEXT></DOC>